               <p>EDWARD COCKERTON sworn. - The prisoner was a <rs id="t18021027-88-deflabel489" type="occupation">chairwoman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18021027-88-defend787 t18021027-88-deflabel489"></join> to me; I live at No. 29, <placeName id="t18021027-88-crimeloc490">Bread-street-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18021027-88-crimeloc490" type="placeName" value="Bread-street-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18021027-88-crimeloc490" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18021027-88-off487 t18021027-88-crimeloc490"></join>: On the 23d of October I missed a tablespoon; the prisoner was asked if she had seen it, and she denied it, and on the Monday following I found it at Mr. Watson's, a pawnbroker, in Watling-street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18021027-88-person790">
                  DAVID 
                  WATSON
               <interp inst="t18021027-88-person790" type="surname" value="WATSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18021027-88-person790" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18021027-88-person790" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a pawnbroker; I took in a table-spoon from the prisoner on the 23d of October; I lent her 8s. upon it; I am sure she is the same person. - (The spoon produced, and identified by the prosecutor.)</p>

               <p>Prisoner's defence. I asked Mrs. Cockerton to lend me a little money, and she said she had none unknown to her husband, and she lent me the spoon till Monday.</p>
               <p>Q. (To Cockerton.) Was Mrs. Cockerton without money? - A. No, I am an oilman, and in a retail shop; it is impossible to be without money.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called three witnesses, who gave her a good character. <rs id="t18021027-88-verdict491" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18021027-88-verdict491" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
